{
  "work_slug": "the-maltese-falcon-by-dashiell-hammett",
  "work_title": "Maltese Falcon, Original Serialized Version",
  "work_author": "Dashiell Hammett",
  "audio_file": "audio-14",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/maltesefalcon_2511_librivox/maltesefalcon_14_hammett.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "Chapter 14 - La Paloma",
  "reader_name": "Mark Nelson",
  "page_num": 4,
  "page_total": 5,
  "page_start_sec": 740.8,
  "page_end_sec": 982.18,
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.707,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 740.8,
      "end": 741.92,
      "text": "He opened the ball carefully,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 742.35,
      "end": 743.72,
      "text": "smoothed it out on the desk,"
    },
    {
      "start": 743.84,
      "end": 745.36,
      "text": "and fitted it into the torn"
    },
    {
      "start": 745.48,
      "end": 746.1,
      "text": "part of the call."
    },
    {
      "start": 746.81,
      "end": 748.8,
      "text": "The fit of the sides was exact,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 749.5,
      "end": 751.72,
      "text": "but between the top of the crumpled fragment and the"
    },
    {
      "start": 751.82,
      "end": 752.8,
      "text": "inferable from Sidney,"
    },
    {
      "start": 753.0,
      "end": 754.5,
      "text": "half an inch was missing,"
    },
    {
      "start": 754.74,
      "end": 757.4,
      "text": "sufficient space to have held announcement of"
    },
    {
      "start": 757.46,
      "end": 758.8,
      "text": "six or seven boats' arrival."
    },
    {
      "start": 760.0,
      "end": 762.68,
      "text": "He turned the sheet over and saw that the other side of the missing",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 762.8,
      "end": 764.88,
      "text": "portion could have held only the meaningless"
    },
    {
      "start": 764.88,
      "end": 766.68,
      "text": "corner of a stockbroker's advertisement."
    },
    {
      "start": 767.61,
      "end": 768.26,
      "text": "Luke,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 768.42,
      "end": 769.54,
      "text": "leaning over Spade's shoulder,"
    },
    {
      "start": 769.68,
      "end": 769.94,
      "text": "asked,"
    },
    {
      "start": 770.816,
      "end": 771.58,
      "text": "What's this all about?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 773.088,
      "end": 775.02,
      "text": "Looks like the gents interested in a boat.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 775.24,
      "end": 775.456,
      "text": "Well,"
    },
    {
      "start": 776.44,
      "end": 777.56,
      "text": "there's no law against that,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 777.68,
      "end": 778.44,
      "text": "or is there?"
    },
    {
      "start": 778.66,
      "end": 781.12,
      "text": "Luke said while Spade was folding the torn"
    },
    {
      "start": 781.24,
      "end": 782.84,
      "text": "page and the crumpled fragment together"
    },
    {
      "start": 782.94,
      "end": 784.84,
      "text": "and putting them into his coat pocket."
    },
    {
      "start": 785.92,
      "end": 787.12,
      "text": "You all through here now?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 787.38,
      "end": 787.48,
      "text": "Yes,"
    },
    {
      "start": 788.74,
      "end": 789.4,
      "text": "thanks a lot,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 789.46,
      "end": 789.64,
      "text": "Luke."
    },
    {
      "start": 790.58,
      "end": 792.0,
      "text": "Will you give me a ring at the office",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 792.12,
      "end": 793.12,
      "text": "as soon as he comes in?"
    },
    {
      "start": 793.34,
      "end": 793.84,
      "text": "Sure."
    },
    {
      "start": 796.448,
      "end": 798.28,
      "text": "Spade went to the business office of the call,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 798.8,
      "end": 800.5,
      "text": "bought a copy of the previous day's issue,"
    },
    {
      "start": 800.76,
      "end": 803.18,
      "text": "opened it to the shipping news page and compared"
    },
    {
      "start": 803.18,
      "end": 805.65,
      "text": "it with the page taken from Cairo's wastebasket."
    },
    {
      "start": 806.24,
      "end": 808.0,
      "text": "The missing portion had read,"
    },
    {
      "start": 808.94,
      "end": 810.24,
      "text": "5.17 a.m.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 810.26,
      "end": 812.12,
      "text": "Tahiti from Sydney and Papidi,"
    },
    {
      "start": 812.96,
      "end": 814.06,
      "text": "6.05 a.m.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 814.16,
      "end": 815.76,
      "text": "Admiral Peoples from Astoria,"
    },
    {
      "start": 816.7,
      "end": 817.8,
      "text": "8.07 a.m.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 818.304,
      "end": 819.66,
      "text": "Catopeak from San Pedro,"
    },
    {
      "start": 820.68,
      "end": 821.88,
      "text": "8.17 a.m.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 822.368,
      "end": 823.78,
      "text": "Silverado from San Pedro,"
    },
    {
      "start": 824.76,
      "end": 825.84,
      "text": "8.05 a.m.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 826.2,
      "end": 827.56,
      "text": "La Paloma from Hong Kong,"
    },
    {
      "start": 828.88,
      "end": 829.98,
      "text": "9.03 a.m.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 829.98,
      "end": 831.52,
      "text": "Daisy Gray from Seattle."
    },
    {
      "start": 832.7,
      "end": 834.32,
      "text": "He read the list slowly,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 835.02,
      "end": 835.87,
      "text": "and when he had finished,"
    },
    {
      "start": 836.04,
      "end": 838.34,
      "text": "he underscored Hong Kong with a four-finger"
    },
    {
      "start": 838.46,
      "end": 838.6,
      "text": "nail,"
    },
    {
      "start": 838.86,
      "end": 841.86,
      "text": "cut the list of arrivals from the paper with his pocket-knife,"
    },
    {
      "start": 842.15,
      "end": 843.12,
      "text": "put the rest of the"
    },
    {
      "start": 843.12,
      "end": 845.36,
      "text": "paper and Cairo's sheet into the waste-basket,"
    },
    {
      "start": 845.48,
      "end": 846.66,
      "text": "and returned to his office."
    },
    {
      "start": 848.22,
      "end": 849.5,
      "text": "He sat down at his desk,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 849.64,
      "end": 851.28,
      "text": "looked up a number in the telephone directory,"
    },
    {
      "start": 851.54,
      "end": 852.54,
      "text": "and used the telephone."
    },
    {
      "start": 854.176,
      "end": 855.06,
      "text": "\"'Kerny 1401,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 855.24,
      "end": 855.54,
      "text": "please.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 856.68,
      "end": 859.744,
      "text": "Where is the Paloma in from Hong Kong this morning docked?\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 859.92,
      "end": 861.64,
      "text": "He repeated the question."
    },
    {
      "start": 862.46,
      "end": 862.92,
      "text": "Thanks.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 863.8,
      "end": 866.58,
      "text": "He held the receiver hook down with his thumb for a moment,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 866.7,
      "end": 867.36,
      "text": "released it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 867.4,
      "end": 867.72,
      "text": "and said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 868.736,
      "end": 869.98,
      "text": "Davenport 2020,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 870.16,
      "end": 870.86,
      "text": "please."
    },
    {
      "start": 871.84,
      "end": 872.4,
      "text": "Detective Bureau,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 872.54,
      "end": 872.84,
      "text": "please."
    },
    {
      "start": 873.9,
      "end": 874.98,
      "text": "Is Sergeant Polehouse there?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 875.66,
      "end": 876.14,
      "text": "Thanks."
    },
    {
      "start": 877.24,
      "end": 877.64,
      "text": "Hello,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 877.74,
      "end": 877.98,
      "text": "Tom."
    },
    {
      "start": 878.08,
      "end": 879.22,
      "text": "This is Sam Spade."
    },
    {
      "start": 879.76,
      "end": 880.18,
      "text": "Yes,"
    },
    {
      "start": 880.24,
      "end": 881.86,
      "text": "I tried to get you yesterday afternoon."
    },
    {
      "start": 882.86,
      "end": 883.06,
      "text": "Sure.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 884.064,
      "end": 885.32,
      "text": "Suppose you go to lunch with me.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 885.6,
      "end": 885.7,
      "text": "Right."
    },
    {
      "start": 887.22,
      "end": 889.34,
      "text": "He kept the receiver to his ear while",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 889.34,
      "end": 890.66,
      "text": "his thumb worked the hook again."
    },
    {
      "start": 892.0,
      "end": 893.76,
      "text": "Davenport 0-1-7-0,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 893.86,
      "end": 894.1,
      "text": "please."
    },
    {
      "start": 895.1,
      "end": 895.32,
      "text": "Hello.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 895.96,
      "end": 897.06,
      "text": "This is Samuel Spade."
    },
    {
      "start": 897.24,
      "end": 900.52,
      "text": "My secretary got a phone message yesterday that Mr."
    },
    {
      "start": 900.6,
      "end": 901.36,
      "text": "Bryan wants to"
    },
    {
      "start": 901.36,
      "end": 901.72,
      "text": "see me."
    },
    {
      "start": 902.76,
      "end": 905.04,
      "text": "Will you ask him what time's most convenient for him?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 905.84,
      "end": 906.26,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 906.48,
      "end": 907.12,
      "text": "Spade."
    },
    {
      "start": 907.5,
      "end": 909.0,
      "text": "S-P-A-D-E."
    },
    {
      "start": 909.82,
      "end": 911.18,
      "text": "A long pause.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 912.2,
      "end": 912.52,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 912.74,
      "end": 913.62,
      "text": "Two-thirty."
    },
    {
      "start": 913.76,
      "end": 914.22,
      "text": "All right."
    },
    {
      "start": 914.34,
      "end": 914.74,
      "text": "Thanks."
    },
    {
      "start": 915.6,
      "end": 917.48,
      "text": "He called a fifth number and said,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 918.43,
      "end": 918.88,
      "text": "\"'Hello,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 918.94,
      "end": 919.18,
      "text": "darling."
    },
    {
      "start": 919.94,
      "end": 920.85,
      "text": "Let me talk to Sid.'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 921.74,
      "end": 922.18,
      "text": "\"'Hello,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 922.18,
      "end": 922.4,
      "text": "Sid."
    },
    {
      "start": 922.54,
      "end": 922.88,
      "text": "Sam."
    },
    {
      "start": 924.14,
      "end": 925.34,
      "text": "I've got a date with the district"
    },
    {
      "start": 925.34,
      "end": 927.5,
      "text": "attorney at half-past two this afternoon."
    },
    {
      "start": 928.74,
      "end": 930.22,
      "text": "Will you give me a ring around four,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 930.46,
      "end": 932.28,
      "text": "there or here or both,"
    },
    {
      "start": 932.42,
      "end": 934.26,
      "text": "just to see that I'm not in trouble?"
    },
    {
      "start": 935.36,
      "end": 937.18,
      "text": "The hell with your Saturday afternoon golf.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 937.36,
      "end": 939.28,
      "text": "Your job's to keep me out of jail."
    },
    {
      "start": 940.32,
      "end": 940.56,
      "text": "Right,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 940.66,
      "end": 940.9,
      "text": "Sid."
    },
    {
      "start": 941.06,
      "end": 941.66,
      "text": "Bye.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 942.82,
      "end": 944.12,
      "text": "He pushed the telephone away,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 944.44,
      "end": 945.16,
      "text": "yawned,"
    },
    {
      "start": 945.16,
      "end": 945.62,
      "text": "stretched,"
    },
    {
      "start": 945.94,
      "end": 947.04,
      "text": "felt his bruised"
    },
    {
      "start": 947.08,
      "end": 947.42,
      "text": "temple,"
    },
    {
      "start": 947.5,
      "end": 950.1,
      "text": "looked at his watch and rolled and lighted a cigarette."
    },
    {
      "start": 950.92,
      "end": 954.1,
      "text": "He smoked sleepily until Effie Perrine came in.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 955.168,
      "end": 956.34,
      "text": "She came in smiling,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 956.62,
      "end": 958.12,
      "text": "bright-eyed and rosy-faced."
    },
    {
      "start": 959.392,
      "end": 961.6,
      "text": "\"'Ted says it could be,' she reported.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 962.28,
      "end": 963.24,
      "text": "\"'And he hopes it is."
    },
    {
      "start": 963.872,
      "end": 965.36,
      "text": "He's going to look it up some more."
    },
    {
      "start": 965.952,
      "end": 968.36,
      "text": "He says he's not a specialist in that field,"
    },
    {
      "start": 968.55,
      "end": 969.74,
      "text": "but the names and dates"
    },
    {
      "start": 969.88,
      "end": 970.38,
      "text": "are all right,"
    },
    {
      "start": 970.46,
      "end": 972.3,
      "text": "and at least none of your authorities"
    },
    {
      "start": 972.3,
      "end": 974.1,
      "text": "or their works are out-and-out fictions."
    },
    {
      "start": 974.38,
      "end": 974.93,
      "text": "He's"
    },
    {
      "start": 975.12,
      "end": 976.32,
      "text": "all excited over it.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 977.344,
      "end": 977.74,
      "text": "That's swell,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 978.06,
      "end": 980.26,
      "text": "as long as he doesn't get too enthusiastic"
    },
    {
      "start": 980.26,
      "end": 981.78,
      "text": "to see through it if it's a lot"
    },
    {
      "start": 981.78,
      "end": 982.18,
      "text": "of hooey."
    }
  ]
}